race.comment: ARTICOLE (3) finished runner-up at Ascot on debut 2 weeks ago in a tougher field than this, and from a good gate, with William Pike keeping the faith, he should go one better. Follow your money. BULLETIN BEAU (1) is a lightly tried 5-year-old gelding who has never had 2 starts in a prep until now. He led up and was only collared late at Bunbury nearly 4 weeks ago as the favourite, and from a good draw, he will take some pegging back again. VIVA MARCONI (2) has been thereabouts lately on this course, and with the aid of a 2kg claim, he is worth including in all combinations. MORF (4) finished runner-up by a short head at Bunbury, fresh up just over a fortnight ago. He strips fitter, and Chris Parnham sticks with him. Each way claims again. LUNA BALLET (7) faded quickly after setting the pace fresh up at Ascot, and should be a lot sharper this time. A senior hoop replaces an apprentice, and an improved run is on the cards.
